<refentry id="bif.Platform" xreflabel="Platform">

<refmeta>
<indexterm>
<primary>Platform</primary>
</indexterm>

<refentrytitle>Platform</refentrytitle>
<refmiscinfo>Built-in function</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>

<refnamediv>
<refname>Platform</refname>
<refpurpose>
Returns a string identifying the system
</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
<synopsis>
Platform[] := TEXT
</synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1><title>Description</title>
<para>
<function>Platform</function>
returns a string identifying the platform that the GCL is
currently running on.  Can be used in user defined functions to define
system dependent variables, such as pathnames and command lines for
shell commands.  
</para>
</refsect1>

